 ============================================================================]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>enableFilter</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ TRUE=apply PT1, FALSE=bypass]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>rawValue</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Input value to be filtered]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>filterTime</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ PT1 time constant]]></Comment><Type>TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>filterGainK</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ PT1 gain, typically 1.0]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>filteredValue</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Filtered (or bypassed) value]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Local><Name>kUse</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>tUse</Name><Type>TIME</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>yPT1</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>_JetToWire</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _JetToWire
 Computes jet speed from wire speed and ratio, then maps to pressure SP (mmH2O).
 Dynamic head: H[mmH2O] = (v^2 / (2*g)) * 1000, with g = 9.80665 m/s^2.
 A tunable gain/offset is applied; SP is clamped to min/max bounds.
 ============================================================================]]></Comment><Parameter><Name>wireSpeedMPM</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Wire speed [m/min]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>ratio</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Jet/Wire ratio (unitless), e.g., 1.05]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>gainK</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Gain on computed head]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>offset_mmH2O</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Offset added to head [mmH2O]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>minSP_mmH2O</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ SP lower bound [mmH2O]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>maxSP_mmH2O</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ SP upper bound [mmH2O]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>jetSpeed_mps</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Jet speed [m/s]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Parameter><Name>autoSetpoint_mmH2O</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ Pressure SP [mmH2O]]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize><Properties><Property><Name>ItemType</Name><Value>Output</Value></Property></Properties></Parameter><Local><Name>wire_mps</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>rUse</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>dynHead_mmH2O</Name><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>cHeadCoeff</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ 1000/(2*g), g=9.80665]]></Comment><Type>REAL</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>_FeedbackDisplay</Name><Local><Name>STATUS_IDLE</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>STATUS_RUNNING</Name><Comment><![CDATA[    STATUS_STARTING : INT := 1;]]></Comment><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Local><Local><Name>STATUS_FAULT</Name><Type>INT</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Local></Method><Method><Name>_SetpointInputControl</Name><Comment><![CDATA[ ============================================================================
 METHOD: _SetpointInputControl
 Purpose: Handle HMI writes and button nudges for both ratio and manual SP,
          using OSCAT TUNE2 instances. External writes trigger a one-scan
          SET pulse; SU/SD remain active every scan.
